keel.Algorithms.Rule_Learning.Swap1

Class InstanceAttributes

  • java.lang.Object
    • keel.Algorithms.Rule_Learning.Swap1.InstanceAttributes

  • public final class InstanceAttributes
extends java.lang.Object

    InstanceAttributes

    This class contains the information of all the attributes in the dataset. It stores the same information in Attributes, but it is not defined as static.
    Version:
    keel0.1
    Author:
    Albert Orriols Puig

      • areAllDefinedAsOutputs

        public boolean areAllDefinedAsOutputs(java.util.Vector outputNames)
        This method checks if all the output names vector corresponds with all the attributes in output vector. If not, it returns a false. It is used in a test to check that the definition of output attributes is the same as the definition made in train.
        Parameters:

      • removeAttribute

        public boolean removeAttribute(boolean inputAtt,
                               int whichAtt)
        It does remove an attribute. Removing an attribute only implies, in terms of Attribute static class, to take it out from the input/output attributes list, but it will never be removed from the attributes general list. So it will be placed as a NON-SPECIFIED attribute, as it wasn't declared in neither @inputs and @outputs definition.
        Parameters:
        inputAtt - is a boolean that indicates if the attribute to be removed is an input attribute
        whichAtt - is an integer that indicates the position of the attribute to be removed.
        Returns:
        a boolean that will be false if the attribute hasn't been found.
